 East London - A joint operation that was conducted by East London Crime Prevention, Flying Squad, POP, K9 and Detective members over the weekend yielded results. According to police spokesperson, Captain Hazel Mqala, one male suspect was arrested for possession of 17 Mandrax tablets at Wosley street, North End, East London. "They also closed six tarvens for non-compliance at Quigney, Southernwood and North End," she said. "A black pistol with a broken trigger was recovered and one male suspect was arrested for Possession of Unlicenced firearm as per Duncan Village case." Capt Mqala said that a 49-year-old male suspect was also arrested at Kalkeni Location for attempted rape of a 19-year-old woman. "People were searched and nine knives were confiscated. A replica firearm was recovered and two male suspects was arrested after a Bussiness Robbery took place at Nompumelelo informal settlement." She added that the members also conducted Vehicle Check Points in Quigney, CBD and Southernwood and six poeple were arrested for Drunken Driving. "All suspects will appear in court soon." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 